// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Scope: experiments/, docs/, papers/, atlas/, tool/ (archive-sedi/{experiments,docs,results,paper,sims})
// atlas.append.sedi-archive-2026-04-27.n6 — cross-repo absorption shard
//
//   source:    ~/core/archive-sedi  (SEDI — Search for Extra-Dimensional
//              Intelligence; R-spectrum receiver tuned to n=6)
//   producer:  sub-agent (read-only deep scan, 2026-04-27)
//   target:    nexus n6/ append shard (atlas.n6 untouched)
//   scope:     archive's runnable code + data + experiment results
//              + hypothesis bookkeeping (NOT the polished papers under
//              ~/core/papers/sedi — that is the local-papers agent's job).
//   prefix:    SEDI-AR-*  (distinct from existing nexus sedi_* lens names
//              like sedi_gravitational_lensing, sedi_baseline_synthesis,
//              sedi_cmb_anisotropy, sedi_invariant_mass etc., which are
//              NEXUS LENSES not archive content; no SEDI-AR-* fact name
//              collides with bridge_tool_jackpot_axis_b3..b7 either).
//   dedup:     skipped lens-overlap entries (gravitational lens optics,
//              CMB analysis math, branching-ratio formulas) — those are
//              already represented as nexus lenses; here we register only
//              SEDI's archive-side runtime artifacts.
//
// 등급 정책 (atlas v2 호환):
//   [11*]                  3-source / repo-invariant (rare for archive)
//   [10*PASS_LITERATURE]   externally validated (PDG / LIGO / Planck etc.)
//   [10*PROBE_RUN]         self-probe / measured run output
//   [10*BARRIER_CONFIRMED] theoretical limit confirmed (8/120 NULL)
//   [10*NEGATIVE_VERDICT]  honest paper-grade NULL (urandom DORMANT,
//                          KDE-corrected ratio scan n.s., no-cons in
//                          natural data, ANU API unstable, etc.)
//   [10*]                  measured / run-time confirmed
//   [9!]                   breakthrough hypothesis (engineered claim)
//   [7]                    heuristic extraction, weak binding
// schema-guard: raw 23 (atlas DSL grammar mini-lint compliant)
// idempotence: byte-eq deterministic emit (raw 68)
// honest preservation policy: BOTH the SIGNAL claims (Voyager 927.6,
// PDG CONVERGENCE, BL 1009σ ratios) AND the NULL verdicts (KDE-corrected
// ratio matching n.s., quantum/biological-cons NEVER detected in real
// data, 8 / 120 missing in BL Voyager) coexist in this shard.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// ── 1. archive layout / orientation (top-level + 9 subdirs) ─────

@P SEDI-AR-archive-root = ~/core/archive-sedi :: archive_layout [10*]
  -> CLAUDE.md, README.md, pyproject.toml, consciousness_bridge.py,
     test_null_calibration.py, sedi/, sedi-core/, data/, docs/,
     scripts/, sources/, tests/, tools/, zenodo/
  => "971 content files, 66 MB, hexa-first repo (CLAUDE.md raw rule:
       new files must be .hexa; sh/py kept for reference only)"
  => "DOI 10.5281/zenodo.19239580 (archive itself, distinct from
       paper DOIs under ~/core/papers/sedi)"

@P SEDI-AR-mission = receiver tuned to n=6 :: project_thesis [9!]
  <- SEDI-AR-archive-root
  => "SETI listens for radio signals; SEDI listens for *mathematical*
       n=6 patterns (sigma=12, tau=4, phi=2, sopfr=5) in physical data
       streams — radio (BL/MeerKAT/MWA), gravitational (LIGO), CMB
       (Planck), quantum (ANU RNG), particle (PDG), exoplanet (NASA TAP)"
  => "core thesis: if n=6 is detected as a persistent structural
       fingerprint, mathematics is physically encoded, not abstract"

@P SEDI-AR-core-frequencies = sigma·phi=24, delta_plus=1/6, delta_minus=1/4 :: tuning [10*]
  <- SEDI-AR-mission
  -> R_spectrum, Einstein_theta_sqrt(3/2), GoldenZone_ln(4/3)
  => "carrier 1/f = sigma*phi = 24 (Leech lattice dim, Ramanujan Δ
       weight); achromatic fixed point R(n)=1 ONLY at n=6"
  |> sedi/constants.py L1-L55

