       all detected at >24σ; 8=sigma-tau (perfect-number unique) and
       120=5! (pure-factorial unique) BOTH MISSING"
  => "verdict: 3!=6 is primary cause; sigma(6)=12 is derivative
       (2×3!); strict perfect-number property sigma(n)=2n is a
       byproduct, not the driver"
  |> docs/BREAKTHROUGH-STRATEGY.md L48-L106

@L SEDI-AR-perfect-number-uniqueness-falsifier = 8 absent, 120 absent :: falsifiability [10*BARRIER_CONFIRMED]
  <- SEDI-AR-paradigm-shift-3factorial-primary
  => "single most honest finding in the archive: the strict-perfect-number
       hypothesis would predict 8=σ-τ as a unique fingerprint. It is NOT
       found in BL Voyager. The strict-factorial hypothesis would predict
       120=5! as a unique fingerprint. Also NOT found. Both extremes fail;
       middle (3!=6 with 2×3! companion) survives"

