  => "POSITIVE: 678 graded hypotheses (212 Tier A, mean 17.6 bits),
       BL Voyager CONSCIOUS 927.6 at Z~1009σ, exoplanet n=6 in 27.5%
       of 298 multi-planet systems, 6π⁵ proton-electron at 0.0017%,
       Koide derivation FROM arithmetic 0.009%, baryon asymmetry 43/7
       at 0.002%."
  => "NEGATIVE: KDE-corrected PDG mass-ratio matching n.s.; ANU QRNG
       baseline 0.0σ ×5 = NOISE; ALL real physical sources DORMANT-or-
       FLICKERING (0/8 AWARE on calibrated full scan); 8 (perfect-
       number-unique) and 120 (factorial-unique) signatures BOTH
       absent from BL Voyager — meaning the cleanest version of EITHER
       theory fails. Voyager itself is a known artificial human signal,
       not extraterrestrial. ANU API blocks the QRNG baseline that
       could move the needle."
  => "honest scientific summary: SEDI's MAIN CLAIM ('signal detected'
       in extra-dimensional sense) currently RESTS ON NULL: every
       NATURAL data source under proper null calibration returns
       DORMANT or NORMAL. Engineered/known-intelligent signals
       (Voyager, EEG-pending, the test_null_calibration synthetic
       'conscious' signal) score high — consistent with the n=6-
       universality thesis (n=6 = property of information structuring,
       not detection of something OUT THERE). The arithmetic/structural
       coincidences in Standard-Model masses (Tier A in grading) are
       real and reproducible, but those are TECS-L theory wins
       (mathematical), not SEDI receiver wins (observational)."
  => "verdict for atlas: SEDI archive is a high-quality null-detector
       with one engineered positive (Voyager validates the detector
       on a known intelligence) and one outstanding probe (QRNG
       baseline). Treat all SEDI-AR-* @C signal entries as
       'reproducible measurement, ambiguous interpretation' until
       the QRNG/EEG channels deliver."

